"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"59c5ab",
"children":[
"Sinus bradycardia is defined as heart rate <50/min. Common causes of inappropriate sinus bradycardia are age-related myocardial fibrosis, hypothyroidism, and inferior ischemia. The most common extrinsic cause is medication use (β-blockers, donepezil, neostigmine, pyridostigmine)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"49a30c",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"atrioventricular",
"children":[
"AV"
]
},
" nodal block results from functional or structural abnormalities at the AV node or in the His-Purkinje system. Potentially reversible causes include acute or chronic myocardial ischemia, Lyme disease, sarcoidosis, and amyloidosis."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_cv_s10_inline_t1",
"mk19_bb_cv_s10_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s10_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9d7f0f",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Sinus bradycardia"
]
},
" requires no treatment for asymptomatic patients. For hemodynamically stable patients with symptoms, treat the underlying condition (e.g., ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"myocardial infarction",
"children":[
"MI"
]
},
","
]
},
" thyroid disease, medications)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"437629",
"children":[
"Initial therapy of AV block includes correcting reversible causes of impaired conduction such as ischemia, increased vagal tone, and elimination of drugs that alter electrical conduction (donepezil, digitalis, calcium channel blockers, β-blockers)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"009acc",
"children":[
"Common indications for permanent pacemaker implantation include absence of reversible cause and:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"77abac",
"children":[
"symptomatic bradycardia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e4e91b",
"children":[
"permanent ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"atrial fibrillation",
"children":[
"AF"
]
},
" and symptomatic bradycardia"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"56d391",
"children":[
"complete heart block"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"90e15f",
"children":[
"high-degree AV block (several consecutive nonconducted P waves)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"07c384",
"children":[
"Mobitz type 2 second-degree AV block"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4d3adf",
"children":[
"alternating bundle branch block"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"909ff0",
"children":[
"Choose IV atropine and/or transcutaneous or transvenous pacing for symptoms of hemodynamic compromise caused by bradycardia or heart block."
]
},
